</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">“Rainbow” like pattern in carriage direction 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Pattern is continually visible in the media direction 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Pattern mainly visible is large uniform colored areas 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Pattern is independent of used print mode 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Pattern is independent of used media 
</p></li></ul><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">ADAM-triggers</b> 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">No ADAM-triggers available. 
</p></section><section id="GUID-DDCC1BB0-B402-4010-9156-67DB737F3DE5" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Analyze/Repair</title><fig id="GUID-4E892DA9-D361-4E9B-9FE8-E4EDA480B0B5" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-2FBDC57A-B0CC-4F63-82E1-95E4574B95DD-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-2FBDC57A-B0CC-4F63-82E1-95E4574B95DD-svg.svg"/></fig></section><section id="GUID-BB9BDDD1-E29C-42C5-BF10-2854E3AE4223" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Steps explanation</title><table pgwide="1" id="GUID-D963269B-E108-446A-A212-4581FEAA8740" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="4" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="10*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="20*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="40*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col4" colnum="4" colwidth="30*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Type 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">To do 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remarks 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Decision 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Check whether the ruler is correctly placed in the guidance 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-77442B9A-25AC-4CE8-9065-AA23BF776D0D" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-C0E36E22-3AB8-4671-9B6C-6CF54F668222-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-C0E36E22-3AB8-4671-9B6C-6CF54F668222-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Place ruler in guidance 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><xref keyref="05DISA007" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-F7547FFE-F473-428E-9370-C8660B61395B.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 05 How to remove the ruler?>05 How to remove the ruler</xref> 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">3
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Decision 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Check whether the spring of the ruler guidance is placed correctly.
</p><p class="- topic/p ">(The spring should be over the plate and NOT touching the edge)
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-7AB2CB14-C3C9-470F-9C2F-0ED608AD5E40" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-A1C29F57-7B0A-49BF-B2C2-28C292349DFD-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-A1C29F57-7B0A-49BF-B2C2-28C292349DFD-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">4
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Reposition the spring.
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">5
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Decision 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Check whether the encoder is placed correctly 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-D0BA7DA8-50CD-4918-B0A0-96EAE35EE6F8" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-826C1BCC-77A1-4822-86A8-6659A8547F64-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-826C1BCC-77A1-4822-86A8-6659A8547F64-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">6
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Reposition the encoder. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><xref keyref="05DISA006" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-4BA51102-8E44-43F4-AB43-A6348585FDE6.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 05 How to remove Y motion system carriage ruler encoder 05PBA03 YMS_CAR_RUL_ENC?>05 How to remove Y motion system carriage ruler encoder ( 05PBA03 ;YMS_CAR_RUL_ENC)</xref> 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Make sure the ruler is in the middle of the encoder and the middle of the print area.
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">7
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Reposition the guidance of the ruler 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Adjust the guidance's position to ensure the ruler is in the middle of the encoder. 
</p></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="GUID-2513E5DF-C282-453D-9841-6E539DB0EB51" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Evaluate/Prevention</title><p class="- topic/p ">There are no specific actions to prevent this issue from happening 
</p></section><section id="GUID-987F83F9-80F0-41BC-B82B-BB16DA268203" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Background info</title><p class="- topic/p ">The color uniformity in carriage direction is dependent on the speed uniformity of the printhead carriage. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">As all printheads are placed beside each other, the buildup of mixed colors is based on the timing/speed of the printhead carriage. If the speed is different than expected the droplets of different colors are placed beside each other instead of on each other. As the printheads in the C1650 are placed in the YCMKMCY pattern, this pattern will be visible if the speed of the carriage is locally slower than expected. In the case of the C1630 MCYK pattern will be visible. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The speed/position of the printhead carriage is determined by the ruler in combination with the Carriage ruler encoder. If the distance between the encoder and the ruler changes too much the detection of position and speed will be incorrect. In most cases, this is due to a loose ruler in the guidance in the middle of the print surface. A loose or misplaced encoder will also lead to unstable position detection. 
</p></section></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-E296D1A5-6E40-45FA-8995-87FBE4000791.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Solutions</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
